contentData.title: Show In Navigation
contentData.value: Toggle true/false if a particular node is going to show in the navigation

contentData.title: umbracoUrlName
contentData.value: This property when created as a text string lets you provide a different URL name to what is created by default by the name of the node. If you enter a value for this property and save/publish the content node you will see that its main URL is updated with a new path suffix.

contentData.title: Super Alias
contentData.value: If used this will take precedence over Umbraco Aliases and URL Structures.

contentData.title: SEO Title
contentData.value: A string value that is used in the pages Meta Data.

contentData.title: SEO Description
contentData.value: A string value that is used in the pages Meta Data.

contentData.title: Show In Sitemap
contentData.value: Toggle true/false determines if the site is listed in the XML and HTML sitemaps.

contentData.title: ogImage
contentData.value: Select and image from the media library and that particular URL will be used for Social Feeds. https://kaydee.net/blog/open-graph-image/

contentData.title: ogDescription
contentData.value: The description that will be used for social feeds.

contentData.title: Canonical URL Content Item
contentData.value: Used to select a page from the content tree. If selected that pages URL will be used in the Meta Data tag for Canonical URL.

contentData.title: Canonical URL Absolute
contentData.value: If the Cananical URL Content Item field is not set than this field can be set. The value of this field must contain the full domain and URL of the canonical field.

contentData.title: Structured Data
contentData.value: Typically provided by the SEO team for each page. Structured data refers to data that is organized in a specific format or structure, typically using predefined schemas or data models. It is characterized by its consistency, uniformity, and well-defined relationships between different elements.
